Normality test

data %>%
  pivot_wider(
    names_from = wave,
    values_from = age) %>%
  select(starts_with("W")) %>%
  shapiro_test(W0, W1, W2)
## # A tibble: 3  3
##   variable statistic        p
##   <chr>        <dbl>    <dbl>
## 1 W0           0.976 3.13e-14
## 2 W1           0.978 1.04e-13
## 3 W2           0.981 2.63e-12
data %>%
  pivot_wider(
    names_from = wave,
    values_from = age) %>%
  select(starts_with("W")) %>%
  mshapiro_test()
## # A tibble: 1  2
##   statistic       p.value
##       <dbl>         <dbl>
## 1     0.988 0.00000000741

Distribution plots

data %>%
  ggplot(aes(sample = age, color = wave)) +
    geom_qq(size = 3, alpha = 0.8) +
    geom_qq_line(linewidth = 2, alpha = 0.6, linetype = "dashed") +
    labs(title = "original age distribution") +
    theme_publish()
